Common transport (MHD) in Prague will introduce the bullet in their ticket system on Wednesday
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, it will be recorded in the history of Pražský Doprevní podnik (the Prague Transport Agency) as the date on which the first passengers, trams and buses, who, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, the latter is accessible to almost one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard Stock.
Passengers can buy a coupon of 30 days or 90 days (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and both will be registered on their card in the information points and offices of the Doprarní podnik (the Transportation Agency), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Nadraží Holeshovice, Andel, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy online coupons on the Doprarní vonnik websites: www.dpp.cz.
Over four hundred people benefited from the service in the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can permanently forget the tickets in the subway stations, where they had to so far become impatient in long queues in order to obtain paper tickets.
In fact, they will buy their coupon via the Internet and they will be registered on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these contact points, there is at the disposal of passengers a geek with trained staff, which will help those interested in buying online and, moreover, will record the coupon they bought on their card," said the spokesman for the Martin Opatrny project.
Alongside libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic cuts on Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, reminding the machines to make the tickets and the passengers have perhaps already noticed them at the Roztyly, Budjejovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro stations.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be twenty-four," Opatrny added.
A machine will control the coupon instead of the driver
